🏋️ Flexora – AI Fitness Trainer

Flexora is an AI-powered mobile fitness application that helps users perform exercises correctly using real-time pose detection and posture correction.

The app combines computer vision, mobile AI, and guided workouts to create a beginner-friendly personal training experience directly on your phone.

🔗 GitHub Repository
https://github.com/SashankGhimire/Flexora

🚀 Features
🤖 AI Posture Detection

Flexora uses MoveNet Lightning (TensorFlow Lite) to analyze exercise form from the camera in real time.

✨ Capabilities

• Real-time pose detection
• Automatic repetition counting
• Posture correction feedback
• Live workout metrics
• On-device AI (no cloud required)

🧠 Supported AI Exercises

• Squat
• Push-up
• Lunge
• Jumping Jack
• Plank
• Bicep Curl

These exercises use body keypoints and motion analysis to detect repetitions and form accuracy.

💪 Guided Bodyweight Workouts (Non-AI)

Flexora also includes guided beginner workout programs.

These workouts help users exercise without AI by following visual animations and audio cues.

✨ Includes

• Exercise GIF / MP4 demonstrations
• Audio workout cues
• Timer-based workouts
• Rep-based workouts
• Muscle focus information
• Common mistake tips

🏠 Example Workout Programs

• Abs Workout
• Arm Workout
• Leg Workout
• Full Body Workout

Users can follow the animations while performing the exercises.

🧠 AI System Architecture

Flexora uses a hybrid AI pipeline combining pose estimation + rule-based motion analysis.

Camera Stream
      ↓
VisionCamera Frame Processor
      ↓
MoveNet Lightning (TensorFlow Lite)
      ↓
17 Body Keypoints Detection
      ↓
Motion Intelligence Layer
      ↓
Exercise Detection
      ↓
Rep Counting & Posture Feedback

The entire system runs directly on the device for fast performance and privacy.

🧍 Pose Estimation Model

Flexora uses MoveNet Lightning, a lightweight pose estimation model optimized for mobile devices.

📄 Model file

movenet_lightning.tflite

📥 Model input

192 × 192 RGB image

📤 Model output

17 body keypoints including:

• shoulders
• elbows
• wrists
• hips
• knees
• ankles

Each keypoint contains:

• x coordinate
• y coordinate
• confidence score

🧮 Motion Detection Logic

Flexora uses rule-based motion analysis to interpret pose data.

The system calculates:

• joint angles
• wrist movement
• hip displacement
• body alignment

Example – Bicep Curl
elbow angle < 60°  → arm bent
elbow angle > 160° → arm extended

Rep counted when movement completes:

down → up → down
📊 User Personalization

After signup, users complete an onboarding questionnaire.

Collected data:

• Fitness goal
• Gender
• Age
• Height
• Weight
• Activity level
• Training preference

BMI Calculation
BMI = weight / (height²)

This information helps personalize workout plans and track progress.

🛠 Tech Stack
📱 Frontend

• React Native
• React Native VisionCamera
• React Native Worklets
• Lottie Animations

🧠 AI

• TensorFlow Lite
• MoveNet Lightning

🌐 Backend

• Node.js
• Express.js
• MongoDB

⚠️ Known Limitations

• Pose detection accuracy may decrease in poor lighting
• Occlusion can affect keypoint detection
• Single-person detection only
• Camera placement affects posture tracking